HLS 26RS-4716 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 315
BY REPRESENTATIVE MARCELLE
WATER/RESOURCES: Urges and requests the Department of Conservation and Energy
to study the establishment of groundwater conservation districts for the Chicot,
Southern Hills, and Mississippi aquifer systems
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Department of Conservation and Energy to study the establishment
3 of groundwater conservation districts for the Chicot, Southern Hills, and Mississippi
4 aquifer systems and to submit a written report of its findings to the House Committee
5 on Natural Resources and Environment prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular
6 Session of the Legislature.
7 WHEREAS, the increasing use of water for municipal, industrial, agricultural,
8 recreational, and other purposes is a matter of great public interest; and
9 WHEREAS, the unregulated use of groundwater from the aquifer systems of the state
10 may create critical and irreversible problems and crucial shortages; and
11 WHEREAS, the public welfare of Louisiana's citizens requires that these vital water
12 sources be put to the highest beneficial use; and
13 WHEREAS, a comprehensive water management plan has been a topic of debate for
14 many years inside and outside of the legislature, but one still has not been adopted; and
15 WHEREAS, the legislative auditor found that Louisiana lacks a statewide water
16 management plan, which would help the state better regulate and value surface water; and
17 WHEREAS, the audit further found that the delay in developing a statewide plan has
18 been caused by the lack of a water code and the need for data on water use; and
