1 WHEREAS, a more robust regulatory process is needed and the establishment of
2 conservation districts for the aquifer systems could provide the much needed oversight for
3 the use of the waters of the state.
4 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
5 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Department of Conservation and
6 Energy to study the establishment of groundwater conservation districts for the Chicot,
7 Southern Hills, and Mississippi aquifer systems and to submit a written report of its findings
8 to the House Committee on Natural Resources and Environment prior to the convening of
9 the 2027 Regular Session of the Legislature.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED the study should consider the use of water for
11 municipal, industrial, agricultural, recreational, and other purposes in Louisiana and how the
12 allocation and costs of that water is being managed and overseen and whether groundwater
13 conservation districts may be utilized in the process.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
15 secretary of the Department of Conservation and Energy.
